the souls of his next victims.","While one might argue that the deadly protrusion on an Alexandrian axe beak's beak has always better resembled a scythe than an axe, the fact of the matter is that they have been and always will be called axe beaks, and not scythe beaks. Except for Scythebeak\u2500the winged monstrosity that roams Exo Alexandria looking to reap the souls of his next victims."]}}}